Os desafios da implantação da Base Nacional Comum Curricular (BNCC) no Brasil: uma revisão de literatura
Abstract: The Federal Council of Educação (CNE) of the Brazilian Ministry of Educação (MEC) has elaborated the Base Nacional Comum Curricular (BNCC) for the National Curricular Common Core, which should be adopted by the 27 federated units of the country and by the 7,000 Brazilian schools, from the Ensino Fundamental (Basic Education) to the Ensino Superior (Higher Education), as well as in the areas of Educação de Jovens e Adultos (EJA) and Educação a distância (EAD). In this paper, we analyzed the literature on the BNCC and on the process of its elaboration, considering the lack of studies on this topic. The bibliographical search was carried out in the Scielo, Scielo Educação and Lattes databases, which allowed to identify 33 articles that were analyzed in the light of the BNCC proposal. The results showed that the BNCC was elaborated considering the guidelines of the National Council of Educação (CNE) and of the National Council of Educação and Culture (CNC). However, the BNCC does not fulfill the demands of the main studies on the topic. The main conclusion of the study is that the elaboration of the BNCC was not supported by the scientific literature. Thus, the BNCC is not adequate for the Brazilian reality and will probably not fulfill its objectives.
Palavras-chave: Base Nacional Comum Curricular, Educação, Ensino Fundamental, Ensino Superior, Ensino a distância, Educação de Jovens e Adultos, CNE, CNC.
